v><div class="t mf95 x61 h2b y2042 ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">6. </div><div class="t m1eb9 xc h2b y1fb3 ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Who then came to Pilate in behalf of the </div><div class="t m23bb x3e h2b y18cd ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">body of Jesus? What was his plea? Verse 38. </div><div class="t m820 x3e h2b y1690 ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">See note 3. </div><div class="t m16f x61 h2b y1d58 ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">7. </div><div class="t m1a2c xc h2b y1bfe ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What did Pilate require to know before </div><div class="t m1f9b x3e h2b y1ce6 ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">granting the request of Joseph? Mark 15 : 44, 45- </div><div class="t ma80 x61 h2b y118d ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">8. </div><div class="t m1fa4 xc h2b y17be ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Who then joined Joseph in preparing Jesus </div><div class="t m28e4 x3e h2b y1d22 ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">for the grave? What did he contribute? John </div><div class="t m284 x3e h2b y18d1 ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">19: 39, 40- </div><div class="t m3e8 x61 h2b y1405 ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">9. </div><div class="t m175e xc h2b y1a03 ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Where did they gently lay Jesus after thus </div><div class="t meb7 x3e h2b y1e7e ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">preparing Him? Verses 41, 42. </div><div class="t m106a x48 h2b y1a06 ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">HD. Who watched the mournful process of put-</div><div class="t m1bbd x3e h2b y1666 ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">ting Jesus in the tomb? Mark 15 : 47- </div><div class="t mcec x48 h2b y1c98 ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">II. After witnessing the burial of their Lord, </div><div class="t m2cd x3e h2b y1760 ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">what did these women do? Luke 23 : 55,56. </div><div class="t m1388 x48 h2b y1b7b ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">12. In the meantime what were the enemies of </div><div class="t m613 x3e h2b y1b3f ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Jesus doing? Matt. 27 : 62-64. </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000